						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold depositedwith the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Arikulakēsarichaturvēdimaṅgalam</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumudukunṟam-Uḍaiyār by <hi rend="bold">Koṇḍanāḍuḍaiyāṉ Kuṉṟaṉ a chief of Paravēḷūr</hi> (?). Arikulakēsari is evidently the same as Ariñjaya the son of Parāntaka I. The inscription may be one of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
